window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>AT THE EDGE OF CHAOS, ONE GEEK STANDS TALL.</b><br> <br> My name’s Bill Ryder. Five years ago, I helped banish magic and monsters to the shadows. I thought it was over, that I was finished with all that supernatural crap. Turns out I was <i>dead</i> wrong.<br> <br> Now the impossible has happened. My goddaughter is conjuring fireballs, I’m seeing ghosts, and two vampires have shown up at my doorstep looking to kick my ass.<br> <br> Seems a group of deranged wizards are hell-bent on reopening the doorway between worlds, once more unleashing unspeakable horrors upon humanity, and they think I hold the secret for how to make it happen.<br> <br> Too bad stopping them will be easier said than done. I'm not a vampire anymore. I'm not anything! I'm just a normal guy living a normal life, facing a seriously abnormal problem. But I need to somehow find a way to end this madness, because otherwise shit's about to get surreal—<b><i>again</i></b>.<br> <br> ----------<br> <br> <i>Strange Days</i> kicks off a thrilling new chapter of <b>The Tome of Bill</b>, the horror comedy series that's left readers hungering for more.<br> <br> If you enjoy <i>Hunter Blain</i>, <i>Steve McHugh</i>, <i>Christopher Moore</i>, or <i>What We Do in the Shadows</i>, then prepare to sink your teeth into the <b>Bill of the Dead Saga</b>!<br> <br> Download <i>Strange Days</i> today and get ready to <i>die</i> laughing! </p> <p><b>Content Warning</b>: This book contains violence, gore, crude humor, and a buttload of swearing.</p>"; 
